  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Element </strong>void; <strong>Type </strong>utility (Sp); <strong>Level </strong>4; <strong>Burn </strong>0<br><strong>Prerequisite </strong>emptiness</p>\n<p>The power of void protects you from curses and allows you to remove or suppress them. You gain a +4 bonus on saving throws against curses and hexes. You can accept 1 point of burn as a standard action to attempt a caster level check to remove a curse on yourself or another as per @Compendium[pf1.spells.o87h8gjxevcbztgd]{Remove Curse}. If the curse normally could not be removed by remove curse, you can instead suppress the curse until the next time your burn is removed with a successful caster level check.</p>\n<p>When your burn is removed, you can choose not to remove the burn you spent in this way to continue suppressing the curse without interruption.</p>\n<p>If you die, any curse suppressed in this way returns instantly.</p>"
    },
